stylometry: Decision trees are the graphical way of making a decisions or decision analysis. They help us to make a decision and interpret the outcome, make a second decision and interpret a second outcome. Decision trees list out the possible decisions, the possible outcomes, and the probabilities of those decision-outcome variables. An example of a decision tree can be used in deciding on whether to invest in a company or not, and they probabilities that come with that. We use yes, no factors, and "always, sometimes, and never" can be used also. The decision tree not only helps you decide but it numerically shows why it would be the best fit decision.
